Disney officials consulted Chinese feng shui experts before building Hong Kong Disneyland, adjusting the park's site and kitchens for harmony.
Plans to serve shark fin soup were scrapped due to environmental concerns.
The park, a joint venture with the Hong Kong government, aims to attract tourists and boost the economy.
However, worries persist about low-spending visitors from China impacting infrastructure.
Despite initial skepticism, ticket sales for the grand opening have been successful.
Rehearsal days are underway, allowing employees to fine-tune performances.
Hong Kong Disneyland is set to open in phases, with special guests and new transport services in place for a smooth start.
